Liar, Liar is a 1993 Canadian drama television movie starring Vanessa King as a girl who accuses her father (Art Hindle) of molestation but no one in her family believes her. The film originally aired in January 1993 on CBC Television in Canada. It aired under the title Liar, Liar: Between Father and Daughter on CBS on June 22, 1993 in the United States. It was also released under the title Daddy's Little Secret in the United Kingdom.